result.execSummary:
The defendant Austin Stephen Healey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Austin Stephen Healey is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Austin Stephen Healey was found guilty of Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Austin S. Healey in court.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  13CM15, 14CF08, 12CM81 called.  Defendant on an imposed & stayed sentence and placed on probation.  Mr. Healey wrote a letter asking to be released from probation and sit jail time.  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant waives right to attorney.    Court revokes probation and in 13CM50 sentence & impose 6 mos. on count 1; 12CM81 sentence & impose 30 days on count 2; 14CF8 sentence & impose 30 days on count 2 all concurrent, credit on all of 2 days.  Jail sentence to commence 3/23 @ 9:00 a.m. with work release, release for education, counseling or treatment.  Court grants judgment for unpaid obligations.  Advised of appeal rights.
Letter from Austin Healey asking to be off probation and sit his jail time.
Refund balance of bond after applying to 12CM81, 13CM50 as ordered.

Defendant Austin Stephen Healey in court with attorney Susan T Falch.   Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty Falch informs the court of agreement.  They do not object to the Motions in 12CM81 & 13CM50.  Count 1 in 14CF08 w/be dismissed, Count 2 will plead guilty with imposed & stayed sentence.

Defendant Austin S. Healey in court with attorney Susan T Falch.  Jon D Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant has several charges before the court.  Counsel rec'd discovery today and requests more time.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for May 6, 2014 at 02:30 pm.
